## [Introduction|280WPM|neutral|0:00-1:10]

### [Overview Block|280WPM|neutral]

Quantum computing asks us to replace familiar intuition with probability, interference, and scale. //
Instead of bits that are either zero or one, /
we work with qubits that preserve richer state until measurement.

## [Why It Matters|300WPM|focused|1:10-2:40]

### [Capability Block|300WPM|focused]

[highlight]The value is not raw speed on every task.[/highlight] /
The value is the ability to model certain classes of problems in a fundamentally different way. //

### [Practical Lens|310WPM|professional]

Chemistry, optimization, and secure systems research are the areas where that difference may become transformative first. //

## [Takeaway|290WPM|motivational|2:40-3:35]

### [Closing Block|290WPM|motivational]

[motivational]The real opportunity is not hype.[/motivational] /
It is building the discipline to understand where quantum methods genuinely outperform classical systems. //
